properties.description: Route of the 9.5 mile Groton Town Forest Race

properties.name: Groton Town Forest Race 3.4 Mile Loop
properties.description: Route of the 3.4 mile Groton Town Forest Race

properties.name: Royal Throne Trail
properties.description: Parking is available off of Rockwood Lane and Castle Drive.

properties.name: Marion Stoddart Nashua River Loop
properties.description: Explore Fitche's Bridge, the Nashua River, and working farms. Parking is available at Hazel Grove Park.

properties.name: Bancroft Castle
properties.description: A short but steep walk up Gibbet Hill to explore the ruins of Bancroft's castle, a expansive westerly view, and Gibbet hill farm. Parking is available at Gibbet Hill Grill during off hours. There is very limited parking off of Rt-40.

properties.name: Hayes Woods Lollipop
properties.description: A lovely short walk around a beaver pond. Parking off of Maple Street.

properties.name: Skinner Pond & Forest Trail
properties.description: Highlights of this walk include Duck Pond, Whitney Pond, and large erratic boulders. Park off of Duck Pond Drive.

properties.name: Shepley Steeplechase Trail
properties.description: Explore dramatic eskers and an abandoned quarry. Park at the Nashua River Rail Trail Parking lot off of Sand Hill Road.

properties.name: Harry's Dark Forest River Trail
properties.description: This flat walk covers the Harry Rich State Forest, with excellent views of the Nashua River and its still oxbows's. Parking is available off of Nod Road.

properties.name: Sabine Woods Loop
properties.description: This walk includes excellent views of the Nashua river, a long easy hill climb, and Groton School boat house. This walk crosses Groton School Property which requires that dogs are on leash. Park at the Long Hill Road parking lot for Groton Place.

properties.name: Mclains/Fitch Woods
properties.description: A lovely flat walk through the woods. Park at Williams Barn.

properties.name: Gamlin Crystal Springs
properties.description: This walk is packed with fun, including Indian rock, wetlands, erratic boulders, an abandoned railroad, and dramatic eskers. Park at the Old Dunstable Raod parking lot.

properties.name: East Groton Tour
properties.description: A long walk covering most of the conservation properties in East Groton. Park off of Dan Parker Road.

properties.name: Indian Hill
properties.description: Park at the Bates Land Parking lot off of Old Ayer Road.

properties.name: Rocky Hill Scenic Walk
properties.description: Explore the Rocky Hill Wildlife Sanctuary, see Long Pond, a heron nesting site, turtles, and the rocky hills. Parking is off of Cardinal Lane.

properties.name: West Groton Tour
properties.description: This is a long hike covering everything in West Groton. See the Nashua river, Fitch's bridge, town forest, the throne, Hazel Grove Park, and Groton School.
